		<td><b>Are unusued bytes of palettes readable &amp; writable?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I've read that unused bytes of the palettes in VRAM, I.E. $3F04, $3F08, $3F0C and their mirrors, are general purpose 6bit registers.
<br />So, they are just 6bit memory positions that can be read and written through $2006 / $2007 ?
<br />Does anyone recall debugging / disassembling a game that used those registers?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


